# Implementation Plan - D-05: Module Hot Swap Pipeline

Implement an atomic, safe hot-swap mechanism for kernel modules as specified in Phase 5 §9.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The hot-swap implementation will utilize a `ShadowBus` proxy to capture and compare events from the candidate module version before switching.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] Module Loader

#### [MODIFY] [loader.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py)
- Implement [hot_swap(module_name: str)](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#236-282) following the 7-step upgrade pipeline.
- Implement `_shadow_load(module_name: str, module_dir: str)`:
    - Loads the module using a `ShadowBus`.
    - Subscribes the shadow instance to mirrored events.
- Implement `ShadowBus` helper class:
    - Proxies [subscribe](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/interfaces.py#151-159) calls to the real [EventBus](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#176-353).
    - Intercepts [publish](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/interfaces.py#147-150) calls to record and compare outputs.
- Implement `compare_outputs()` logic:
    - Ensures the shadow module produces compatible event sequences for a set of test/mirrored events.

#### [MODIFY] [registry.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/registry.py)
- Ensure `update_status` and `update_version` support atomic transitions.

### [Component] Tests

#### [NEW] [test_module_hot_swap.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/tests/test_module_hot_swap.py)
- Verify shadow loading with event mirroring.
- Verify successful switch when outputs match.
- Verify automatic rollback when healthcheck or output comparison fails.
- Verify old version cleanup (shutdown + unsubscribe).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `pytest tests/test_module_hot_swap.py -v`
- `pytest tests/test_module_loader.py -v` (ensure no regressions in standard load/unload)

### Manual Verification
1. Load version 1.0.0 of a module.
2. Trigger [hot_swap](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#236-282) to version 1.1.0.
3. Observe mirrored events in audit ledger.
4. Verify the active instance ID changes after the swap.
